---
import ChapterLabel from "./ChapterLabel.astro";
import Timeline from "./Timeline.astro";
---

<section
	class="bg-[var(--color-bg-light)] px-6 py-16 sm:py-[var(--spacing-section-y)]"
	aria-labelledby="the-research-title"
>
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-[var(--width-content)]">
		<p
			class="animate-on-scroll mb-4 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-xs tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--color-text-muted-dark)]"
		>
			10+ years of research &middot; 200+ published papers
		</p>

		<ChapterLabel title="The Research" id="the-research-title" />

		<p
			class="animate-on-scroll stagger-1 max-w-[var(--width-paragraph)] font-[var(--font-body)] text-lg leading-[1.7] text-[var(--color-text-dark)]"
		>
			Grid Foresight Lab began at the University of Calgary with a simple question: can machine
			learning forecast energy demand better than the methods the industry has relied on for
			decades?
		</p>

		<p
			class="animate-on-scroll stagger-2 mt-6 max-w-[var(--width-paragraph)] font-[var(--font-body)] text-lg leading-[1.7] text-[var(--color-text-muted-dark)]"
		>
			Under the leadership of Dr. Hamidreza Zareipour, a team of researchers spent over a
			decade answering that question. They published hundreds of papers, trained thousands of
			models, and tested their methods against real-world grid data.
		</p>

		<Timeline />
	</div>
</section>
